',{id:"us_organic_farmland_share_by_state",title:"Organic farmland as share of total farmland by state 2022 - the geography of the organic transition",sub:"California: 4.2% of farmland certified organic - the highest in the US. Vermont: 3.8%. Maine: 3.1%. Nebraska: 0.3%. Mississippi: 0.1%. The organic geography follows premium market access - states with dense urban populations nearby and high-income consumers have the strongest organic conversion incentive.",type:"MAP",geo:"us_state",fmt:"State choropleth",tbl:"USDA NASS Organic Survey 2022 (public, quinquennial)",section:"Agriculture",ext:["ACS 5-year estimates: MHI, poverty rate, population by geography (Census API - free, tidycensus)","BEA Regional: GDP + personal income per capita by state (apps.bea.gov - free)","Census Population Estimates: annual population by state/county (census.gov - free)","USDA ERS: food environment, rural classification, farm income (ers.usda.gov - free)"],vars:["avg_farm_size","farm_net_income_state"],join:["median_household_income","pct_bachelors","population_pct_change"],sc:{emotional:5,relatability:6,surprise:6,tension:3,visual:6,data_ready:8,originality:5},vs:54,tags:"organic farmland share state 2022 California 4.2% Vermont 3.8% Maine 3.1% Nebraska 0.3% Mississippi 0.1% premium market urban high-income USDA NASS Organic Survey"}',
